    "body": "Some `class Sock`  tests were previously disabled because Windows lacks [`socketpair(2)`](https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/socketpair.2.html). This PR adds a `CreateSocketPair()` helper for Windows which imitates [`socketpair()`](https://github.com/torvalds/linux/blob/1896ce8eb6c61824f6c1125d69d8fda1f44a22f8/net/unix/af_unix.c#L1830-L1859), and  enables these test cases for Windows.\r\n\r\nThis change is generally an improvement, but is also broken out of a [branch](github.com/davidgumberg/bitcoin/tree/2025-09-02-0xB10C-prefill-rebase) that does compact block prefilling up to the available bytes in the connection's current TCP window (see [delving post](https://delvingbitcoin.org/t/stats-on-compact-block-reconstructions/1052/34)). \r\n\r\nBeing able to create pairs of sockets is needed for testing some of the new interfaces needed for querying the current TCP window state, and without this change those tests don't run on Windows.",
