      "body": "The changes refactor the `CreateSocketPair` function to provide a cross-platform implementation and improve the handling of `Sock` objects using `std::unique_ptr` and move semantics, enhancing test robustness and memory management.\r\n\r\n**Key Changes:**\r\n- Introduced a Windows-compatible implementation for `CreateSocketPair` using TCP loopback connections, as `socketpair(2)` is not available on Windows.\r\n- Modified `CreateSocketPair` to return `std::pair<Sock, Sock>` instead of modifying an integer array, promoting RAII and better ownership semantics.\r\n- Replaced raw pointer usage (`new Sock(...)`) with `std::unique_ptr` in `send_and_receive` and `wait` test cases for safer memory management.\r\n- Leveraged structured binding (`auto [sock0, sock1] = ...`) for cleaner initialization of socket pairs in test cases.\r\n- Removed the `ifndef WIN32` block around the `CreateSocketPair` declaration, making it a single function with conditional logic inside.\r\n- Ensured that `Sock` objects are properly moved and managed, especially after move assignment, in the `send_and_receive` test.\r\n\r\n",
