      "body": "## ⚠️ Code Issue\r\n\r\n**Lines:** 107-117\r\n\r\n```cpp\r\n    Sock* sock0 = new Sock(s[0]);\r\n    Sock* sock1 = new Sock(s[1]);\r\n\r\n    SendAndRecvMessage(*sock0, *sock1);\r\n\r\n    Sock* sock0moved = new Sock(std::move(*sock0));\r\n    Sock* sock1moved = new Sock(INVALID_SOCKET);\r\n    *sock1moved = std::move(*sock1);\r\n\r\n    delete sock0;\r\n    delete sock1;\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis code snippet demonstrates manual memory management using `new` and `delete` for `Sock` objects. This is error-prone and can lead to memory leaks if not handled meticulously. Modern C++ practices advocate for RAII and smart pointers to manage resource lifetimes automatically.",
